# ðŸ”§ FireGuard AI â€” Hardware Setup

This guide explains how to *connect and configure the hardware* for the FireGuard AI fire detection system.

---

## ðŸ“‹ Components Required
- *ESP32* (38-pin recommended)
- *MQ-2 Gas & Smoke Sensor*
- *DHT22 Temperature & Humidity Sensor*
- *IR Proximity Sensor* (optional)
- *Active Buzzer*
- Breadboard & jumper wires
- USB cable for ESP32 connection
- Power source (via USB or regulated supply)

---

## ðŸ“Œ Pin Connections

| Component            | Pin on Sensor | ESP32 Pin | Notes |
|----------------------|--------------|-----------|-------|
| *MQ-2*             | VCC          | 3.3V      | Use 3.3V for ESP32 compatibility |
|                      | GND          | GND       |       |
|                      | A0           | GPIO 34   | Analog input |
| *DHT22*            | VCC          | 3.3V      |       |
|                      | GND          | GND       |       |
|                      | Data         | GPIO 4    | Requires pull-up resistor (10kÎ©) |
| *IR Sensor* (opt)| VCC          | 3.3V      |       |
|                      | GND          | GND       |       |
|                      | OUT          | GPIO 27   | Digital input |
| *Buzzer*           | +            | GPIO 25   | PWM-capable pin recommended |
|                      | -            | GND       |       |

