## âš™ Power Considerations
- The ESP32â€™s *3.3V pin* can power the sensors.
- If adding more components, use an *external power supply* (regulated 3.3V) to avoid instability.
- Avoid powering the MQ-2 from 5V when connected to ESP32 analog pins.

---

## ðŸ”Œ Steps to Assemble
1. Place ESP32 on a breadboard.
2. Connect each sensor according to the table above.
3. Double-check VCC and GND connections â€” wrong polarity can damage components.
4. Connect the buzzerâ€™s + pin to GPIO 25, - pin to GND.
5. Plug ESP32 into your computer via USB.
6. Upload the Arduino .ino file from the hardware/ folder.

---

## âœ… Testing Hardware
1. Use individual sensor test scripts before full integration.
2. Open Arduino Serial Monitor at *115200 baud*.
3. Verify each sensor outputs expected values before running the AI model.

